description:
# Task

Add BAML type re-exports to dspy-rs lib.rs so macros can reference them.

## File to Modify
`crates/dspy-rs/src/lib.rs`

## Re-exports to Add

```rust
// Re-export baml-bridge crate for power users
pub use baml_bridge;

// Derive macro
pub use baml_bridge::BamlType;

// Core types from baml_types
pub use baml_bridge::baml_types::{
    BamlValue, Constraint, ConstraintLevel, ResponseCheck, TypeIR, StreamingMode,
};

// Output format for schema rendering
pub use baml_bridge::internal_baml_jinja::types::{OutputFormatContent, RenderOptions};

// Parse flags for metadata
pub use baml_bridge::jsonish::deserializer::deserialize_flags::Flag;

// Conversion error type
pub use baml_bridge::convert::BamlConvertError;
```

## CRITICAL: Verify Export Paths

Before implementing, verify these paths compile:
1. `baml_bridge::internal_baml_jinja::types::OutputFormatContent` - MAY need to be added to bridge re-exports
2. `baml_bridge::jsonish::deserializer::deserialize_flags::Flag` - verify public

If not exported, add to `baml-bridge/crates/bridge/src/lib.rs`:
```rust
pub use internal_baml_jinja::types::OutputFormatContent;
pub use jsonish::deserializer::deserialize_flags::Flag;
```

## Testing Strategy

```rust
#[test]
fn test_reexports_compile() {
    // Verify all re-exported types are accessible
    let _: dspy_rs::TypeIR;
    let _: dspy_rs::BamlValue;
    let _: dspy_rs::OutputFormatContent;
    let _: dspy_rs::Flag;
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
1. All re-exported types compile and are accessible via dspy_rs:: prefix
2. Flag type is importable (either re-exported or via full path)
3. OutputFormatContent is accessible
4. cargo check passes for dspy-rs crate
